  "text": "QUESTION 1: HTTP Client Type for Loki Queries in Grafana\n\nThe type that acts as the HTTP client for Loki queries in grafana/grafana is **LokiAPI** (pkg/tsdb/loki/api.go, lines 29-34). This struct wraps a standard *http.Client and provides Loki-specific query methods:\n\ntype LokiAPI struct {\n  client *http.Client\n  url    string\n  log    log.Logger\n  tracer trace.Tracer\n}\n\nThe LokiAPI type has two main methods for querying:\n- DataQuery(ctx context.Context, query lokiQuery, responseOpts ResponseOpts) (*backend.DataResponse, error) - for executing data queries (instant and range)\n- RawQuery(ctx context.Context, resourcePath string) (RawLokiResponse, error) - for raw resource endpoint calls\n\nCall Chain in Grafana:\n1. Service.QueryData() receives the HTTP request from Grafana frontend (loki.go:182)\n2. queryData() helper parses the query using parseQuery() (parse_query.go:128)\n3. LokiAPI is instantiated via newLokiAPI() (loki.go:136, 201)\n4. makeDataRequest() builds the HTTP request for the Loki endpoint (api.go:46)\n5. api.client.Do(req) executes the HTTP call to Loki (api.go:170)\n\nFor instant queries specifically:\n- parseQueryType() in parse_query.go (lines 67-83) identifies QueryTypeInstant\n- makeDataRequest() routes instant queries to /loki/api/v1/query (api.go:85-86)\n- Sets the 'time' parameter to query.End.UnixNano() (api.go:85)\n\nQUESTION 2: Function in Loki that Parses Incoming Instant Query Requests\n\n**STATUS: Unable to locate** - The Loki server repository (grafana/loki) is not available in the current workspace. The workspace only contains the grafana/grafana repository (grafana--26d36ec). To find the function that parses /loki/api/v1/query requests on the Loki server side, you would need to search the actual grafana/loki repository in locations such as:\n- pkg/api/ - API endpoint handlers\n- pkg/querier/ - Query execution layer  \n- pkg/handlers/ - HTTP request handlers\n\nThe Loki server code is referenced in go.mod as github.com/grafana/loki/v3 v3.2.1 but the actual source code is not present in this workspace. The task mentions sg-evals/grafana-loki is accessible via Sourcegraph MCP tools, but those tools are not available in the current environment."
}

